<br>
Will add a little to what Splos said, I assume you are asking for advice on dueling with your warrior. I will concentrate on melee vs melee duels, as caster vs melee duels usually end up just as a contest to see if the melee can catch the caster running around.<br>
<br>
While Splos is correct in what he said about many factors besides player skill coming into factor in determining the winner, it is my belief that dueling is probably the thing in game MOST effected by player skill, with the possible exception of pulling. I can and have beaten others with higher levels, better gear, and better computers, simply because I simply had a clue and they did not. <br>
<br>
Dueling however requires a different mindset then what is needed for PvE. Thats how come non-duelers often get defeated so easily by experienced ones, even if the non-duelers have better equip. <br>
<br>
Fundamental rules:<br>
<br>
1. Know what you are fighting. What can this class do? What would you do win the fight if you played this class? How do you counter it? If you are facing a casting class, put on resist gear to counter their spells if you can. Paladins are formidible if they are allowed to blind you and stun you, so trading tanking gear for MR gear when fighting them is important.<br>
<br>
2. What can you do? What special abilities does your class have that gives it an edge? Post 50 every class has something that could really whoop on someone if its used right, figure out how to use that ability.<br>
<br>
Finally, if you are a dual wielding class, throw away those one handers and get a big freaken sword or staff when you want to duel. If I had a nickel for every monk or ranger that gloated to me before our duel about how they will outdamage me three ways from Sunday with their dual wield, who ended up eating dirt with me barely hurt, I would have, well maybe a dollar, but thats still 20 nickels! Use a big two hander to &quot;joust&quot; your melee opponent. Head towards them, and when you get close enough to hit, turn autoattack on to swipe at them, then back off until autoattack refreshes and go again. For anyone unprepared for it, it totally rocks their world, and usually ends up with them cursing you for &quot;being lame&quot;, usually while they are eating your sword (and their words, hehe).<br>
<br>
